        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "The underlying bug is in pandas [this bug](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/31063). So, the return type of `df.groupby(...).apply(...)` can be a dataframe if the number of unique groups in `df` (`df` here refers to the first argument of `_groupby_slice_apply` ) is just 1.\r\n\r\nOne possible solution is that we look out for this pandas bug in `_groupby_slice_apply` and convert the dataframe back to a series. That is, check if the number of groups is 1, check if the return type is a df, if so, call `df.stack` before returning it.\r\nJust a workaround until the pandas issue is resolved. @jrbourbeau do you see some problems with this? \r\n\r\n",
